<P>
THE COWBOY AND THE GOOD OL' GIRL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Can someone please explain why, when Ann Richards divorced, it was considered a 
"failed marriage." 
</P>
<P>
Yet when writing about Williams, I quote, "Along the way, he married, fathered 
two daughters, then divorced in 1964." The writer, making it sound as if 
Williams' divorce was just a stroll through the park, feeds into the so-called 
macho image. It appears to me that J. Michael Kennedy has a little of the same 
prejudice that has made Clayton Williams so popular in Texas. 
</P>
<P>
ROBERT OLIVER 
</P>
