RED AND BLACK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
As an honorary member of the Iroquois Confederation, I applaud Kevin Costner's 
film "Dances With Wolves." 
</P>
<P>
It's a long bow shot better than its antecedents ("A Man Called Horse," etc.) 
in capturing the Sioux Indian Nation's culture. 
</P>
<P>
Now what next? Well, for every white who took the blanket, there were at least 
a hundred of another American culture -- and color -- who did. I'm referring to 
Afro-Americans. They joined many Indian tribes. 
</P>
<P>
