<P>
'STRETCHING' ON FILM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
If all actors let their "star" persona limit them, we would have missed out on 
great performances such as Harrison Ford's in "Witness" and Mary Tyler Moore's 
in "Ordinary People." 
</P>
<P>
When star actors are discouraged from taking risks, many unfortunately resort 
to roles that are far beneath them. 
</P>
<P>
What if all artists' careers were controlled by their fame? Picasso would have 
stayed in his blue period and the Beatles would have been fun-lovin' mop-tops 
who never gave us "Sgt. Pepper's Lonely Hearts Club Band." 
</P>
