<HEADLINE>
<P>
ERMA BOMBECK: LET ROSEANNE BE NO BARR TO PEACE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ERMA BOMBECK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I haven't heard too many solutions for the problems in the deserts of the 
Mideast. Oh, there was that bad joke about how President Bush was going to send 
1,000 women with PMS because they were not only mean as snakes but they also 
could retain water. But other than that, no one has come forward with a plan. 
Until a few weeks ago. 
</P>
<P>
An Italian politician and porn star, Illona Staller (a.k.a. La Cicciolina), has 
volunteered to sleep with Saddam Hussein if he agrees to free the foreigners he 
is holding in Iraq. 
</P>
<P>
I feel like a fool. The only thing I could come up with was to cut down on my 
gas consumption by car-pooling. 
</P>
<P>
The radical member of Parliament's offer is a dramatic one, but I have to ask 
myself: Where was Illona when we were dealing with the old Ayatollah Khomeini 
or the Zits Squad -- Gen. Manuel Noriega, Moammar Kadafi and Yasser Arafat? If 
this is to be a viable solution to our global problems, we can't pick and 
choose whom to sleep with. 
</P>
<P>
Actually, I was surprised to see this offer come from Italy. It's usually the 
French who make love, not war. The English, on the other hand, would have 
countered with, "Let's sit down over a nice cup of hot tea." The Italians 
traditionally would have said, "Relax. I'll make you a nice dinner." 
</P>
<P>
The Americans? We don't really make sacrifices until we are pushed into a 
corner. But we can do it. We can bite the bullet if we have to. There's an 
entire generation out there without any idea of what we did to win World War II 
on the home front. For four years, my grandmother saved her fat in large coffee 
cans. I don't know what she ever did with it, but someone told her to do it and 
she did. Nylon was being used for parachutes, so women used makeup on their 
legs and painted a seam up the back with a pencil. On a hot day, the makeup 
melted and your legs looked like someone turned up the heat in a wax museum. 
</P>
<P>
We had ration stamps for sugar, coffee, shoes and gasoline. I don't recall 
anyone stepping forward and volunteering to sleep with Hitler or Tojo. 
</P>
<P>
On Thanksgiving, President Bush unveiled his secret weapon for peace. He said 
he considered sending Roseanne Barr to Iraq to sing "The Star-Spangled Banner." 
Before you discard that idea, remember what happened to Noriega when he hid out 
in the Vatican embassy and our soldiers played rock music at 140 decibels? 
</P>
<P>
Maybe our options come down to Illona or Roseanne. 
</P>
</TEXT>
