<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: PASADENA; 
</P>
<P>
PARKING BAN SURVEY MAILED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Questionnaires about the city's ban on overnight parking have been mailed to 
6,000 randomly selected Pasadena households. 
</P>
<P>
City Directors are re-evaluating the 35-year-old ordinance that prohibits 
parking on city streets between 2 and 6 a.m. The re-evaluation began after the 
city stepped up enforcement in July to aid street-sweeping operations and some 
recipients of $20 tickets complained. 
</P>
<P>
The questionnaires must be returned by Dec. 17. The board will discuss the 
ordinance in February. 
</P>
