<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA120990-0047 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 319603 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
December 9, 1990, Sunday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
San Gabriel Valley; Part J; Page 2; Column 1; Metro Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
131 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: POMONA; 
</P>
<P>
SMITH STUDIES REELECTION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Mayor Donna Smith, who last month said she plans to seek a third term, now says 
she is reevaluating whether to run again. 
</P>
<P>
Smith's son Sean, an 18-year-old Army private, suffered severe burns Nov. 8 
while lighting a stove at a training base in Virginia. 
</P>
<P>
Smith said she has been so preoccupied by her son's injuries that she hasn't 
had time to think through her own plans. 
</P>
<P>
Smith has more than two weeks in which to make up her mind. Candidates for 
mayor and four City Council seats must file papers by Dec. 27. 
</P>
<P>
By mid-afternoon Thursday, 10 candidates had taken out nominating papers for 
the March 5 municipal election, including Councilman Tomas Ursua, who is 
running for mayor, and Councilwoman Nell Soto, who announced that she will seek 
reelection in the 1st District. 
</P>
</TEXT>
