LONG BEACH WOMEN WIN TITLE, 90-64 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Kari Parriott had 25 points and a career-high 19 rebounds Saturday night to 
lead the 11th-ranked Cal State Long Beach women to a 90-64 victory over Kansas 
State in the championship game of the Dial Soap tournament at University Gym. 
</P>
<P>
Dana Wilkerson added 14 points and Trise Jackson had 13 as the 49ers improved 
to 4-1. Kansas State, led by Diana Miller's 28 points, fell to 3-3. 
</P>
<P>
Long Beach, which had a 64-32 rebounding edge, broke open a tight game by 
scoring the last eight points of the first half to take a 43-33 lead. 
