<P>
PREP BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
PARKS SCORES 34, BUT TUSTIN BEATS MARINA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BOB BORSUM 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Solid first-quarter play and execution helped Tustin High School defeat Marina, 
67-50, for the title in the second Trabuco Hills High School basketball 
tournament Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
Tustin (4-0), led by David Beilstein's 22 points, took an 18-4 lead with 2:11 
left in the first quarter and never looked back. 
</P>
<P>
Beilstein shared co-most valuable player honors with Cherokee Parks of Marina. 
</P>
<P>
"We played solid man-to-man defense and double-teamed Parks down at the post," 
Tustin Coach Tom McCluskey said. "We played relaxed, we concentrated on what we 
wanted to do and we executed well." 
</P>
<P>
Parks, who scored 34 points for Marina (3-2), made two free throws with 6:49 
left to cut Tustin's lead to 11 points, 52-41. 
</P>
<P>
In the Trabuco Hills Tournament: 
</P>
<P>
Los Alamitos 56, Mater Dei 55 -- In the fifth-place game, Los Alamitos (4-2) 
handed the Monarchs their second loss in the past three games and second in the 
past 30. 
</P>
<P>
Capistrano Valley 71, J.W. North 57 -- Tom Airey scored 10 of his 19 points in 
the fourth quarter to lead Capistrano Valley. Brett McCorkle scored 21 points 
for Capistrano Valley. 
</P>
<P>
Mission Viejo 84, University 77 -- Mark Wright scored 21 points to lead Mission 
Viejo in the fifth-place game. BOB BORSUM 
</P>
</TEXT>
