<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
DIVISION IX 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARTIN BECK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Whittier Christian 34, Tehachapi 21 -- Whittier Christian's defense slowed 
Tehachapi just enough to pull out a victory in Bakersfield. 
</P>
<P>
Whittier Christian (13-0) had no turnovers and forced Tehachapi (12-2) into 
three turnovers, each leading to a touchdown. 
</P>
<P>
Herald tailback Rex Pritchard rushed for a touchdown in each half, quarterback 
Nick Sanchez threw a 49-yard touchdown pass and ran for a four-yard score, and 
fullback Carl Martinez had a seven-yard touchdown run in the third quarter that 
gave the Heralds a 27-21 lead. 
</P>
<P>
Tehachapi running back Eric Young, who rushed for more than 2,000 yards in the 
regular season, gained 182 yards in 30 carries and scored a touchdown. MARTIN 
BECK 
</P>
