<HEADLINE>
<P>
OLD FRIENDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Kathie Jenkins 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Entering these restaurants is like taking a trip in a time machine. 
</P>
<P>
Bob Burns, 202 Wilshire Blvd., Santa Monica. (213) 393-6777. 
</P>
<P>
Style: Where lovers of old-time American/Continental go for huge helpings. 
Setting: Scottish cornball. Recommended: Caesar salad; royal steak-o-bob; 
gravlax. Cost per person: $18-$45. 
</P>
<P>
Chez Jay, 1657 Ocean Ave., Santa Monica. (213) 395-1741. Style: Funky old-fogy 
serving great steaks and scampi. Setting: Old nautical, with blaring jukebox. 
Recommended: Scampi; butter steak; New York steak. Cost per person: $15-$30. 
</P>
<P>
Knoll's Black Forest Inn, 2454 Wilshire Blvd., Santa Monica. (213) 395-2212. 
Style: Standard German with a twist, and a wine list that's a happy surprise. 
Setting: Tacky Teutonic -- deer heads, beer steins, cuckoo clocks -- ask to sit 
on the patio. Recommended: Smoked salmon soup; cold fried herring with 
marinated raw onions and cucumber pickles; sauteed calf's liver with fried 
onions and apple rings. Cost per person: $20-$30. 
</P>
<P>
Rangoon Racquet Club, 9474 Little Santa Monica Blvd., Beverly Hills. (213) 
274-8926. Style: Burmese food for big bwanas. Setting: Colonial gentlemen's 
club, with ceiling fans and jungle-scene mural. Recommended: Woody's world 
championship chili; Rangoon crab and shrimp lumpia; chicken hash. Cost per 
person: $25-$50. 
</P>
<P>
The Tower Restaurant, 1150 S. Olive St., Los Angeles. (213) 746-1554. Style: 
Old-fashioned food at modern prices. Setting: A room with a view. Recommended: 
Louisiana crab cake; peppered Atlantic salmon; rack of lamb. Cost per person: 
$20-$45. Kathie Jenkins 
</P>
