is 45% over capacity, bed down in a day room that serves as a dormitory at 
night. ; Photo, Charles Drake, above, senior detention officer and unit leader 
at the facility in Sylmar, heads a team watching over juvenile inmates during 
the day. Linda Janssen, right, who teaches math, science and health, waits 
outside her room as youths pass on their way to class. Students are checked by 
teachers before they enter the classroom. ROLANDO OTERO / Los Angeles Times; 
Photo, Youth who has a private room strips bed for last time after being told 
he's going to youth camp. 
