<HEADLINE>
<P>
PASSENGER, 17, KILLED IN SYLMAR CAR CRASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 17-year-old Sylmar youth was killed Saturday when a car he was riding in hit 
the center divider of Truman Avenue at San Fernando Road in Sylmar, then 
careened into a wall, Los Angeles police said. 
</P>
<P>
Jose Ignacio Diaz was riding in the back seat of the car when the crash 
occurred at 12:30 a.m., Sgt. John Amott said. 
</P>
<P>
Another passenger, who was not identified, suffered moderate injuries, but was 
released after being treated at Holy Cross Medical Center, he said. 
</P>
<P>
The driver of the vehicle, who reportedly had a bloodied face, and another 
passenger apparently fled the scene after the crash, Amott said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
