<P>
EL SEGUNDO TOURNAMENT STARTS MONDAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The El Segundo High/Kiwanis boys' basketball tournament, featuring nine South 
Bay teams, will begin Monday with four games. 
</P>
<P>
Top local entries include defending champion Bishop Montgomery, Leuzinger, 
Hawthorne, South Torrance and Mira Costa. In the most attractive first-round 
matchup, Bishop Montgomery will meet Hawthorne at 4:30 p.m. Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
The tournament continues through the week, with the championship final at 7:30 
p.m. Friday. 
</P>
<P>
