<HEADLINE>
<P>
TRUCK HITS 18 VEHICLES ON NIMITZ FREEWAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
HAYWARD 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A man who claimed God told him he could drive through cars with his flatbed 
truck collided with 18 vehicles and injured about 12 people Saturday on the 
Nimitz Freeway, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
A two- to three-mile section of highway was littered with dented vehicles 
before Emmett Wheat, 47, hit the center divider with his truck. 
</P>
<P>
An 8-year-old girl suffered the most serious injuries when she was thrown from 
her mother's van when it was struck. Francesca Camus of Hayward was 
hospitalized in critical condition. 
</P>
<P>
Other injuries were minor, according to the California Highway Patrol. Wheat, 
owner of Commercial Auto Wreckers in San Leandro, has been booked on suspicion 
of felony hit-run driving and driving under the influence of alcohol, police 
said. 
</P>
