<HEADLINE>
<P>
WOMAN DIES AFTER BEING STRUCK BY A PICKUP TRUCK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WESTMINSTER 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Midway City woman who was struck Friday night by a pickup truck as she tried 
to walk across a busy intersection has died, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Helen May Bowden Bender, 48, was crossing Bolsa Avenue at Purdy Street when the 
6:09 p.m. accident occurred, Westminster Police Sgt. Bob Amren said. 
</P>
<P>
Bender was in the crosswalk at the intersection, which has no signal or stop 
sign, Amren said, when the driver of a 1988 blue Chevy pickup failed to see 
her. 
</P>
<P>
It is not known how fast the truck was traveling when it struck her, Amren 
said. 
</P>
<P>
Bender was taken to UCI Medical Center in Orange with internal injuries. She 
died at 11:30 p.m., the county coroner's office said. 
</P>
<P>
The driver, Patrick Vigil, 68, of Westminster, was not cited. 
</P>
