</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Charles Solomon 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DR. KOOKIE, YOU'RE RIGHT! By Mike Royko (Plume: $8.95). This latest collection 
of Chicago Tribune columns confirms Mike Royko's position as one of the 
guardians of respectable American yahooism, a position he shares with Andy 
Rooney. 
</P>
<P>
There's something patently false about a Pulitzer Prize-winning writer posing 
as an everday Joe Sixpack who hangs out with his buddy, Slats Grobnik, but 
Royko plays the role to the hilt. He rails against anti-smoking crusaders, 
lawyers, yuppies (although he admits he lives like one), health food and 
feminism: "But even the most hard-nosed of feminists must concede that during 
the past two decades, great strides have been made. I know dozens of women who 
swear better than me." Royko's blue-collar persona allows him to vent otherwise 
unacceptable prejudices under the guise of just-one-of-the-boys goodfellowship. 
Charles Solomon 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Book Review; Column 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA120990-0211 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 320292 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
December 9, 1990, Sunday, Home Edition 
